---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="SDK reference">
  <article class="doc">
    <div class="eyebrow">Docs / 03</div>
    <h1>SDK reference</h1>
    <p class="intro">Use the same Rust rule engine inside editors, CI jobs, and document workflows.</p>
    <h2>Lint text</h2>
    <pre>use lawlint_core::&#123;lint, LintOptions&#125;;

let result = lint(
    text,
    &amp;LintOptions &#123;
        disable: Some(vec!["no-legalese".into()]),
        ..Default::default()
    &#125;,
);</pre>
    <p>Add <code>lawlint-core</code> as a path dependency from this repository in your Rust project. The SDK is pure Rust and does not perform file or stdin I/O.</p>
    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <p>Configuration-file discovery belongs to the CLI. The core SDK accepts <code>LintOptions</code> directly, including <code>enable</code>, <code>disable</code>, <code>severity</code>, and <code>thresholds</code>.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
<style>
  .doc { max-width: 48rem; padding: 6rem 0; }
  .doc h1 { max-width: 12ch; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .doc h2 { font-size: 2rem; margin-top: 3.5rem; }
  .intro { color: var(--muted); font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 2rem 0 4rem; }
  .doc li { margin: 0.8rem 0; }
  code { font: 0.86em "IBM Plex Mono", monospace; }
  .doc pre { margin: 1.2rem 0; }
</style>
